                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1215/406.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Officer of the United States in charge of the
                            maintenance of the status quo in the Chamizal Tract</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I enclose herewith for your information a copy of
                    a note<note n="1" xml:id="d1250fn1">Of January 30.</note> from the Ambassador of
                    Mexico at this capital, stating that the Government of Mexico is of the opinion
                    that there was no violation of the status quo in the Chamizal Tract in the
                    recent ejection of occupants of land therein intended for the Pearson
                    establishment.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
